description.narrative: UNICEF continued to play a pivotal role in behaviour and social change efforts in Rwanda. Over five million people were reached with key messages on stunting prevention, responsive caregiving, gender equality, maternal and child health, sanitation and hygiene, and positive discipline. To communicate these messages, UNICEF used channels like social media, community theatre, mass media, outreach through mobile vans, group discussions, partnerships with religious leaders, radio programmes like Urunana and Itetero, and home visitation. Prevention and response efforts for Ebola and COVID-19 reached over six million people in across the country using similar channels. . | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/08/2020
